Did it in crocs

Last week my mom died. It’s been the worst week of my life. What makes it even harder is that it’s the also been the worst week for most of the people I love. If you’re reading this, there’s a pretty good chance my mom knew and loved you too. She kept up with everybody. She would even call me sometimes just to talk about a comedian she saw online and see if I could tell them she was a fan. We talked all the time, but now it feels like not nearly enough. She sent me a Bible verse every morning. She sent me Steve Harvey clips almost as often. She did everything she could to brighten my day, and everyone else’s. She was always the funniest person in the room. She taught me everything I know, and reminded me of that regularly. Usually with some sort of royalty demand. I don’t think there was ever a time I couldn’t reach her. She was always there to talk for as long as I wanted. And as long as she wanted. Anybody with a good mom knows that feeling. No matter what was going on in the world, there was a woman in Royston who was there for me. Who would do anything for me. There’s a short list of people who are rock solid. But I could always count on her. And I did. A lot. 

If you take a baby’s mom away from them for two seconds, the baby cries. My mom’s been gone from this world for a week, and the only way I’ve been able to cope is with the help of other people who are hurting just as much as me. I love my mom so much. I’m gonna miss her like you wouldn’t believe. I lost a mom. But a wife was lost, and sister, and a friend to so many people. I can’t thank the people who have been there for me this week to cry with, hug, and talk with. The messages and love and food that me and family received this week is overwhelming. If anybody who knew her wants to talk, let me know. The talking helps.

I had a woman in Royston my whole life until a week ago. Moms are a very special thing. If you’ve got a good one, there’s a woman in a town that’s there for you. Take care of her. Hug the people you love. Tell them you love them. It’s the best thing in life
